CONSTRUCTORS:

=> How to create a constructor:

a) The name of the constructor will always be same as the name of the class to which it belongs
b) The constructor will not have any return type including void

public sameNameAsTheClassName()
{
   logic
}

=> How is Constructor called
   Its called automatically the moment we create object of the class. So we don't have to call
   Constructors explicitly like non static variables/methods or static variables or methods

